          "reviewRating": {
            "@type": "Rating",
            "ratingValue": "1",
            "bestRating": "5",
            "worstRating": "1"
          },
          "reviewBody": "The teacher turn around is too high. They keep removing the teachers without any reason....first time in the history of schools the new principal has taken this drastic step of laying off several existing teachers to accommodate the other favourite ones. Seems to be too political....how will the small kids adjust to this turnover of teachers? \n\nThe reasons given were so lame n they couldn't even face the teachers....they started saying teachers resigned.\n\nI really don't understand how trained and qualified teachers can be removed as incapable while untrained teachers have been recruited inspite of not performing the demo sessions well n not with good communication skills.\n\nAs we understand, they are trying to take new teachers with less salary to save money. If this is the case, how will the quality be maintained?\n\nIs it the real value for our money we get if we put our wards here in this school????\n\nPlease think twice before opting this school.",
          "publisher": {
            "@type": "Organization",
            "name": "Yellow Slate"
          }
        },
        {
          "@type": "Review",
          "itemReviewed": {
            "@type": "School",
            "name": "Casagrand International School - Perumbakkam"
          },
          "author": {
            "@type": "Person",
            "name": "craftyexclusive Madhu"
          },
          "datePublished": "2025-03-22",
          "reviewRating": {
            "@type": "Rating",
            "ratingValue": "5",
            "bestRating": "5",
            "worstRating": "1"
          },
          "reviewBody": "Casa Grande Perumbakkam is truly one of the best schools in OMR. Due to certain personal reasons, my son has studied in almost all the top schools in the area, and we finally found the perfect fit here.\n\nWhat stands out the most is the incredibly caring and friendly staff, teachers, and even the principal. Everyone is humble and approachable, creating a warm and supportive environment. My son enjoys every single day at school so much that he even wishes to go on weekends!\n\nHis class teacher, Ms. Angel, is exceptional in handling children and ensures that every student feels cared for. The teaching methods are excellent, and my son learns something new every day. He used to be quite addicted to mobile games, but after informing his teacher, she immediately addressed it. The very next day, she advised him not to use the phone, and from that moment on, he completely stopped—he hasn’t touched it since!\n\nThe academics, teaching approach, and overall atmosphere at the school are outstanding. Hats off to the entire team for creating such a wonderful learning environment!",
          "publisher": {
            "@type": "Organization",
            "name": "Yellow Slate"
          }
        },
        {
          "@type": "Review",
          "itemReviewed": {
            "@type": "School",
